    "long_instructions": "### Reusing Functions\r\n\r\nNico was experimenting with how different background beats sound with classical music. He started started writing his code with the main theme and taking beats from the `Hip Hop` and `Heavy Metal` packs, but now he's ready to pause and turn some of his code into functions\r\n\r\n> I think I can make a function for the **main theme** since it shows up twice. Then I can have a function for my **Hip-hop beats** and another for my **Heavy metal beats**\r\n\r\nCan you help Nico adjust his code? You'll need to define 3 functions and call them 4 times (so one function is called twice!)\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/c274c781ce91455f69ed5f57380a66b6-image-1745874643246.png)",
